The paper deals with remote sensing image retrieval using fully convolutional networks (FCN) and region convolutional features. This involves computer vision techniques such as image segmentation and feature extraction, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques such as similarity measure and multi-label classification, which are typically covered in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of FCN and region convolutional features also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for multi-label remote sensing image retrieval, which involves the use of deep learning and semantic understanding of images, suggesting a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
